65
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:37,440
So yes, our title this time is

66
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,440
Where Will It All End?

67
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,520
We've seen, haven't we,

68
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,320
in these previous three lectures

69
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,160
how the Old Testament shapes

70
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:45,080
the identity and the mission

71
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,880
and the ethic of God's people.

72
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,520
Those of us who are in Christ,

73
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,280
as Paul says in Galatians,

74
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,800
are in Abraham.

75
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,160
We are part of that people

76
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,280
believing Jews and Gentiles.

77
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:58,440
And we are shaped together

78
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,400
by the scriptures as a whole,

79
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,160
the scriptures of our Lord Jesus Christ,

80
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,200
of course, what we now call the Old Testament.

81
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,040
So the Old Testament then,

82
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,520
topped by the New,

83
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,160
tells us who we are,

84
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,680
why we are here,

85
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,600
and how we are to live.

86
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,120
That's what we've been thinking about

87
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,280
over the three lectures.

88
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,120
But what's the point?

89
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,120
Where is it all going to end?

90
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,040
Where does this story go?

91
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,720
All human religions and philosophies

92
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,960
and ideologies

93
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:29,840
express some elements of narrative or story

94
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,280
to explain how things are

95
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,440
and how they got to be the way they are

96
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,360
and how we could make them better

97
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,280
if we want to.

98
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:40,720
And the Bible as a canonical whole,

99
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,640
the whole scripture that we have,

100
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:45,480
is also in that sense a narrative,

101
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,440
indeed, a metanarrative.

102
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,440
It tells the big story

103
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,800
that runs from creation,

104
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,600
right through to new creation,

105
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,520
from Genesis to Revelation.

106
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,640
But it's not just a story.

107
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:01,080
It claims to be the story,

108
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:03,760
the true story of the whole universe.

109
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,720
Now,in other places

110
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,000
and in some of my books,

111
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,280
I've tried to pick up an idea

112
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,480
that I first got from,

113
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,520
well,originally from Tom Wright

114
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,000
and then from Michael Goheen

115
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,080
and Craig Bartholomew,

116
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,800
who talk about the Bible

117
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,760
as rather like a great drama,

118
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,840
that is a great cosmic play

119
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:23,520
that has taken several acts,

120
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,520
you know how dramas

121
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,600
have different acts,

122
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,680
in which God is the author

123
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:29,760
and, of course, the chief character,

124
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,960
but there's a cast of thousands as well.

125
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,400
And one way in which

126
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,080
I've tried to portray this

127
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,600
is in a kind of diagram

128
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,600
which I put into

129
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,720
one of my other books

130
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,720
called The Great Story

131
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,120
and the Great Commission,

132
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,000
which is published by Baker,

133
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,960
like this, with sort of symbols

134
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,560
that express the different acts

135
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,280
of the Bible.

136
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,280
So here it is

137
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,640
as a drama in seven acts.

138
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,600
I'll try to go through this

139
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,160
fairly quickly, watching my time,

140
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,280
because I'm very aware

141
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,960
that there are two of us this evening.

142
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,000
Act one of the Bible story,

143
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,760
of course, is the creation.

144
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,640
In the beginning,

145
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:02,400
God created the heavens and the earth.

146
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,320
And I've put this as a triangle

147
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,240
because there is God.

148
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,120
He created the earth

149
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,360
and he put human beings in it.

150
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,520
Act one, all a good start.

151
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,720
But then, of course,

152
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,080
we know that everything went wrong

153
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,720
because we chose

154
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,560
to rebel against our Creator,

155
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,160
to distrust his goodness,

156
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,280
to disobey his instructions.

157
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,160
And so that symbol expresses

158
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,240
the sense of rebellion.

159
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,920
Act two of the story

160
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,560
is where all the problems begin.

161
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,960
And then act three is basically

162
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:29,400
the rest of the Old Testament.

163
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,960
It's a very long act

164
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,760
and there's an awful lot in it.

165
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,080
And it's not just a story.

166
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,920
Of course, it's full of other things

167
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,240
like poetry and psalms

168
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,280
and wisdom and everything else.

169
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,880
But the arrow pointing forward

170
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,920
has this sense of movement

171
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:45,160
that it is going somewhere

172
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,760
because it's based on

173
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,560
God's promise,

174
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,080
the promise that he made to Abraham

175
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,120
that he would be a nation

176
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,120
and through him the nation

177
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:52,760
is to be blessed

178
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:53,800
as we've been thinking

179
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,040
repeatedly through these

180
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,280
last couple of days.

181
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,600
Act three, therefore,

182
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,160
is a story which ultimately

183
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,640
leads up to act four,

184
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,400
which, of course, is the coming

185
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,680
of the Lord Jesus Christ

186
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,280
when the God of Israel

187
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,400
keeps his promise,

188
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,120
enters into human history

189
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,000
as a human being,

190
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,280
the Word becomes flesh

191
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,480
and then lives and teaches,

192
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,960
dies the atoning death

193
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:15,600
on the cross

194
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:16,960
and rises again

195
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,560
and returns to his father.

196
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:21,080
So that cross symbol at the centre

197
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:23,440
is not just the crucifixion

198
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,640
but is intended to represent

199
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,640
everything we have in the Gospels,

200
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,000
from the conception

201
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,280
by the Holy Spirit

202
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,800
through to the ascension

203
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,440
of the Lord Jesus Christ.

204
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:35,200
But the Bible doesn't end there,

205
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,080
does it? Of course not.

206
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,960
It moves on through the book of Acts

207
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,480
into the outpouring of God's Spirit

208
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,280
on his people,

209
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,840
sending the people of God

210
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,800
out in mission

211
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,920
to the ends of the earth.

212
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,040
We live within that era of mission

213
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,320
begun in the New Testament

214
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,960
and continuing to this day,

215
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,720
which leads to the last two

216
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,240
great acts of the story.

217
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,920
I put a tick here

218
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,080
for the final judgment.

219
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,760
It might seem a wrong symbol,

220
00:07:58,760 --> 00:07:59,480
but in a sense,

221
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,520
that is when God puts everything right.

222
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:04,560
It's when God deals with evil,

223
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,680
so evil will not have the last word.

224
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,280
Thank God.

225
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,640
The judgment is actually good news

226
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,880
in Paul's thinking

227
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:13,080
because it is when God rectifies

228
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,200
all that went wrong

229
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,360
in the story.

230
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,400
And that then leads

231
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,480
to the new creation,

232
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,680
the new heavens and the new earth

233
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,120
that we read about there

234
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,360
in Revelation 21 and 22,

235
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,680
but of course actually promised

236
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,440
in the book of Isaiah.

237
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,080
Now,that's simply trying to portray

238
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,720
the whole Bible story

239
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,800
on the back of an envelope,

240
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,480
in a sense,

241
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,400
which is where I first saw it done,

242
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,400
actually with a friend of mine

243
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,840
in the US with some other

244
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,840
slightly different symbols,

245
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,800
but the same idea.

246
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,040
I've even done this

247
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,160
on the back of a napkin

248
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:43,120
in a restaurant

249
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,320
sitting beside somebody

250
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:45,360
and say,

251
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,600
what do you think the whole Bible is?

252
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,920
Well,just draw it like this.

253
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,360
Here's the whole story of the Bible

254
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,960
in one piece.

255
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,160
And this helps us to see,

256
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:53,600
of course,

257
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,080
that we now,

258
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,480
we are somewhere in Act 5,

259
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,200
that is to say,

260
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,520
we are in between

261
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,160
the resurrection of Christ

262
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,320
and the return of Christ.

263
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,120
We are in the Bible.

264
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,160
Did you know you're in the Bible?

265
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,040
We are.

266
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,560
We are actually participating

267
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,480
in this drama.

268
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,600
We are part of the story.

269
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,320
This is the story we are in.

270
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,600
And of course,

271
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,280
this Act 5 is not the end.

272
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,880
We know that ultimately

273
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,280
this story is leading

274
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,840
to a glorious future,

275
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,640
which gives us hope.

276
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:22,560
That's why I use the word hope

277
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,000
in the title of the lecture.

278
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,760
Now,hope,of course,

279
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:27,400
is one of those massive

280
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,880
New Testament words.

281
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:29,600
In fact,

282
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,840
the Apostle Paul puts it

283
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,960
in his favourite three,

284
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:32,520
doesn't he?

285
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,120
Now abide faith,

286
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,680
hope and love.

287
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,360
But Christian hope

288
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,040
is not just optimism.

