00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,400
So that was simply

551
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,400
a kind of a glimpse

552
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,840
at Romans 15.

553
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,880
It's a significant passage.

554
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,240
Please don't overlook it

555
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,960
because you can't get past

556
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,000
Romans 9 to 11

557
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:37,520
or something.

558
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,560
It's a very important way

559
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:41,320
in which Paul draws his letter

560
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,440
to a conclusion.

561
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,000
So I want us to think of this

562
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,240
hope then, the God of hope,

563
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,160
briefly in three areas.

564
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:48,920
As I said, hope for sinners,

565
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:50,320
hope for the nations,

566
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,800
and hope for creation.

567
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,320
So first of all then,

568
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,520
hope for sinners

569
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,920
goes, takes us right back,

